How about accepting that they aren't really valuable in the game the way it has evolved? They were conceived when VI thought multi mob encounters would be the standard. Sadly a lot of our spells are tuned for multi mob encounters. Hell even McQuaid said as much in his last 'AskBrad' (tm).<br>
<br>
Frankly, I'd love them to re-evaluate all our aoes:<br>
<br>
a) Make rains single target with lower resist. The weakness being that the mob needs to stay stationary for the duration of the spell (which can take skill).<br>
<br>
b) Add more pillars, the level range and damage types are too limited.<br>
<br>
c) Scrap Al'Kabors. They are just padding.<br>
<br>
Of course if they scrapped Al'Kabor spells our spell books would be the most empty of the pure casters by an even greater margin.<br>
<br>
Just my take, but I'm trying to be pragmatic and I just don't see the place for wide range slow aoes in a game where aggro control is where its all at.<br>
<br>
 <p>Cassius Runeblaze <Avatars of Discord><BR>
lvl 56<BR>
Rodcet</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usorinspellcaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorin Spellcaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 3:51:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How would you fix the Al'Kabor line?</span><hr size=1> How about if you increased the maximum number of targets effected to, for example 6, and added a concussion effect, so soloing you would still agro all the MOBs but when working in a group with tanks, you would only agro those that resisted.<br>
